The paper focuses on generating imaginary videos from a single image, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) techniques. The proposed framework uses transformation generation and volumetric merge network, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) fields. The paper also mentions unsupervised learning and adversarial training, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
